# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# NuxtHub × bunny.net — Environment Variables
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values.
# In dev mode, everything works without any config:
#   Database → local SQLite at .data/db/sqlite.db
#   KV/Cache → filesystem at .data/kv/ and .data/cache/
#   Blob     → filesystem at .data/blob/
#   Sessions → in-memory
#
# On bunny.net Magic Containers, set these as
# container environment variables at deploy time.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── Site URL ───────────────────────────────────────────
NUXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL=http://localhost:3000

# ── Database (Bunny Database / libSQL) ─────────────────
# NuxtHub detection: TURSO_DATABASE_URL → LIBSQL_URL → DATABASE_URL → local file
# Bunny Database uses libSQL protocol, so use LIBSQL_URL
# Dev:  leave empty → auto local SQLite at .data/db/sqlite.db
# Prod: Bunny Database dashboard → Access → Generate tokens
# LIBSQL_URL=libsql://your-db.lite.bunnydb.net
# LIBSQL_AUTH_TOKEN=your-database-token

# ── Redis (multi-container sidecar) ────────────────────
# NuxtHub detection: UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL → REDIS_URL → filesystem
# Dev:  leave empty → KV/Cache use filesystem, sessions use memory
# Prod: Redis 7-alpine sidecar on Magic Containers (127.0.0.1:6379)
# REDIS_URL=redis://127.0.0.1:6379

# ── Blob Storage (S3-compatible / Bunny Storage) ───────
# NuxtHub detection: S3 vars → BLOB_READ_WRITE_TOKEN → filesystem
# Dev:  leave empty → local filesystem at .data/blob/
# Prod: Bunny Storage zone credentials
# S3_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-storage-zone-name
# S3_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-storage-zone-password
# S3_BUCKET=your-storage-zone-name
# S3_REGION=sg
# S3_ENDPOINT=https://sg-s3.storage.bunnycdn.com

# ── Bunny CDN (image optimization) ────────────────────
# Used by @nuxt/image Bunny provider in production
# BUNNY_CDN_URL=https://your-pullzone.b-cdn.net

# ── Bunny API ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Account-level API key for bunny.net management APIs
# BUNNY_API_KEY=your-account-api-key

# ── Bunny Stream (video demo) ─────────────────────────
# Video Library ID and Video ID for the embedded player demo
# Get these from your Bunny Stream dashboard
# NUXT_PUBLIC_BUNNY_STREAM_LIBRARY_ID=your-library-id
# NUXT_PUBLIC_BUNNY_STREAM_VIDEO_ID=your-video-id

# ── Auth (nuxt-auth-utils) ────────────────────────────
# Session encryption secret (generate: openssl rand -hex 32)
# NUXT_SESSION_PASSWORD=your-session-secret-min-32-chars

# ── OAuth (optional) ──────────────────────────────────
# NUXT_OAUTH_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=
# NUXT_OAUTH_GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=

# ── Nuxt Studio Auth (optional) ────────────────────────
# Self-hosted content editing via Nuxt Studio
# Option A: GitHub OAuth (same app works for both site auth and Studio)
# STUDIO_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=your-github-client-id
# STUDIO_GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=your-github-client-secret
#
# Option B: External SSO server
# Requires: https://github.com/nuxt-content/nuxt-studio-sso
# STUDIO_SSO_URL=https://auth.example.com
# STUDIO_SSO_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id
# STUDIO_SSO_CLIENT_SECRET=your-client-secret

